{"word":"H3784 - כָּשַׁף - kâshaph - kaw-shaf' - Sorcerer","slug":"H3784","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">כָּשַׁף</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>kâshaph"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>kaw-shaf'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Sorcerer"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05DB;&#x05BC;&#x05E9;&#x05C1;&#x05E3; - ka&#x0302;shaph</b> - <i>kaw-shaf'</i><p/>A primitive root; properly to <i>whisper</i> a spell, that is, to <i>inchant</i> or practise magic: - sorcerer, (use) witch (-craft)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H3785\">H3785</a>, <a href=\"#/H3786\">H3786</a>"}]}